GEMINI-TERMINAL-PYTHON3(1)        User Commands        GEMINI-TERMINAL-PYTHON3(1)

NAME
    gemini-terminal-python3 - Bash terminal Gemini client with Python 3 helpers

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-terminal-python3 [session_name]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --resume <session_name>
    gemini-terminal-python3 --list
    gemini-terminal-python3 --rename-session OLD NEW
    gemini-terminal-python3 --models [--all]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --models --sort input-tokens
    gemini-terminal-python3 --update-models
    gemini-terminal-python3 --test-model <model_id> [--save]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --select-model [--save]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --config
    gemini-terminal-python3 --set KEY VALUE
    gemini-terminal-python3 --unset KEY
    gemini-terminal-python3 --set-api-key
    gemini-terminal-python3 --forget-api-key
    gemini-terminal-python3 --show-memory <session>
    gemini-terminal-python3 --edit-memory <session>
    gemini-terminal-python3 --clear-memory <session>
    gemini-terminal-python3 --editor-prompt [session]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --attach FILE [session]
    gemini-terminal-python3 --credits
    gemini-terminal-python3 --doctor
    gemini-terminal-python3 --version
    gemini-terminal-python3 --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-terminal-python3 is the practical line-oriented Bash edition of
    gemini-terminal-tools.  It uses Bash for orchestration and Python 3 helper
    snippets for JSON, URL quoting, attachment handling, config-safe parsing,
    and other tasks that are fragile in shell alone.

    It is not the same as the Bash-only edition.  This version favors reliability
    while remaining lighter than the ncurses interface.

USAGE
    First-time setup:

        gemini-terminal-python3 --set-api-key
        gemini-terminal-python3 --update-models
        gemini-terminal-python3 --select-model

    Start a timestamped chat:

        gemini-terminal-python3

    Start or reopen a named chat:

        gemini-terminal-python3 android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        gemini-terminal-python3 --resume android-backup

    List sessions:

        gemini-terminal-python3 --list

    Show effective config:

        gemini-terminal-python3 --config

    Set config value:

        gemini-terminal-python3 --set CONTEXT_TURNS 20

INPUT
    Type or paste a message, then press Ctrl+D to send.  Ctrl+C exits.

MODEL WORKFLOW
    Model discovery uses the Gemini models endpoint and filters metadata rather
    than guessing future model names.

        gemini-terminal-python3 --models
        gemini-terminal-python3 --update-models
        gemini-terminal-python3 --test-model gemini-2.5-flash
        gemini-terminal-python3 --select-model

CONFIGURATION
    Shared config file:

        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    Important keys:

        MODEL, CONTEXT_TURNS, GEMINI_API_KEY, SESSION_DIR, ATTACHMENT_DIR,
        EDITOR, MODEL_TEST_PROMPT, MAX_ATTACHMENT_BYTES, STARTUP_NOTICE,
        MODEL_FILTER_GENERATE_CONTENT, MODEL_FILTER_REQUIRE_TOKENS,
        MODEL_FILTER_HIDE_PREVIEW, MODEL_MIN_INPUT_TOKENS,
        MODEL_MIN_OUTPUT_TOKENS, MODEL_SORT_ORDER

MEMORY
    The client stores and rebuilds rolling conversation context using session
    logs and memory snapshots.  CONTEXT_TURNS controls how many recent
    user/assistant exchanges are sent back to Gemini.

ATTACHMENTS
    The client can extract fenced code blocks from Gemini output into attachment
    files and can attach local files to prompts.  Media support depends on model
    and API capability.

DIAGNOSTICS
    --doctor checks local readiness without printing API key values.

VERSION
    gemini-terminal-python3 version 2.9

AUTHOR
